      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Continuum linear-elastic model with frictional contact at screw-rod and rod-block interfaces; geometry derived from manufacturer CAD; model form justified by literature and prior FDA validation studies.",
      "rationale": "Linear-elastic continuum FEA with Coulomb friction (mu=0.2 at Ti-alloy interfaces) selected based on sub-yield loading regime confirmed by experimental data. Model form consistent with FDA-validated approach in Nagaraja et al. 2019. Geometry imported directly from DePuy Synthes CAD files. Meets required level 3."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Material properties (Ti-6Al-4V, PEEK rod) sourced from ASTM standards and manufacturer data sheets; geometric dimensions measured on physical specimens and compared to nominal CAD; uncertainty in inputs quantified.",
      "rationale": "Ti-6Al-4V elastic modulus 114 GPa per ASTM F136; PEEK rod modulus 4.0 GPa per manufacturer CoC. Dimensional measurements on 5 physical screws showed <0.3% deviation from CAD nominal. Input uncertainty propagated via Monte Carlo (N=1000); coefficient of variation on stiffness QoI was 1.4%. Meets required level 3."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "N=11 constructs tested; samples drawn from production lot; dimensional inspection confirms conformance to design specification; traceability to lot records maintained.",
      "rationale": "Eleven constructs assembled from a single production lot of non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screws (DePuy Synthes lot 2018-NC-75). Pre-test dimensional inspection confirmed all screws within ±0.05 mm of nominal. Lot traceability records archived. Meets required level 3."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Multiple test conditions (e.g., varying load offsets or fixture configurations) to characterize model performance across the COU space; environmental conditions controlled and documented.",
      "rationale": "Testing performed at a single ASTM F1717 standard condition (62 mm offset, room temperature, displacement-controlled at 5 mm/min). Only one test condition was evaluated due to resource constraints, resulting in achieved level 2 below required level 3. This gap is acknowledged; the single condition corresponds to the most clinically relevant loading scenario. Accepted with documented limitation."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Model input parameters (geometry, material, boundary conditions) demonstrably equivalent to test specimen parameters; any discrepancies quantified and their effect on QoIs assessed.",
      "rationale": "Specimen-specific geometry measurements fed into individual FEA instances for all 11 constructs. Torque-controlled assembly replicated in FEA via pretension elements calibrated to measured clamp loads. Discrepancy analysis showed maximum 1.1% deviation in stiffness attributable to residual geometric mismatch. Meets required level 3."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison using E/uval metric (acceptance bound E/uval < 1.96) and percentage difference (<10%) for all three QoIs; results reported with experimental uncertainty.",
      "rationale": "E/uval values: stiffness 0.84, yield force 1.21, force at 40 mm 1.07 — all below 1.96 threshold. Percentage differences: stiffness 3.2%, yield force 6.8%, force at 40 mm 4.1% — all below 10% bound. Experimental uncertainty estimated via inter-lab variability (CV 4.3%). Meets required level 3."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs (stiffness, yield force, force at 40 mm displacement) directly linked to clinical failure modes and regulatory submission requirements per ASTM F1717.",
      "rationale": "Construct stiffness predicts load-sharing behavior relevant to adjacent segment disease; yield force maps to fatigue endurance limit; force at 40 mm corresponds to post-yield structural integrity. All three QoIs are explicitly required by ASTM F1717 and referenced in FDA guidance for spinal implant 510(k) submissions. Meets required level 3."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
