    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors meet or exceed required levels. The single deficiency (Test conditions, achieved 2 vs. required 3) is accepted because the single ASTM F1717 condition evaluated is the most clinically representative loading scenario and the quantitative output comparison metrics (E/uval < 1.96, QoI difference < 10%) are satisfied across all three quantities of interest at both laboratories. Overall credibility is sufficient to support a Medium assurance level conclusion for this Class II device submission.",
